  <body>
    <div class="example" id="variables-and-constants">
      <h2><a href="index.html">Crystal by Example</a>: Variables and Constants</h2>
      
      <table>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>To store a value for later, simply assign it to a name with the equals operator</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
           <div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="n">some_var</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">&quot;a value&quot;</span>
</pre></div>

          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>You can specify the type of a value after a space-separated colon and before the assignment operator</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
           <div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="n">another</span> <span class="p">:</span> <span class="nb">Float32</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">3</span>
</pre></div>

          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>If the name of a value starts with a capital letter, that name represents a constant which can't be reassigned</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
           <div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="no">CONST_VALUE</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">123.456</span>
</pre></div>

          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>By convention, all variables are in lower_snake_case, constants are in UPPER_SNAKE_CASE, while type names use PascalCase</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code empty">
           
          </td>
        </tr>
        
      </table>
      
